\begin_inset Formula $[l_{1},r_{1}]$
\end_inset

.
 Assume that another disjoint event 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{2}$
\end_inset

 has interval probability 
\begin_inset Formula $[l_{2},r_{2}]$
\end_inset

, what is the interval probability of the event 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}\cup E_{2}$
\end_inset

? The answer is somewhat subtle: although it is possible to use the sum
 of the intervals 
\begin_inset Formula $[l_{1}\tensor*[_{\mathbb{R}}]{+}{}l_{2},r_{1}\tensor*[_{\mathbb{R}}]{+}{}r_{2}]$
\end_inset

 as the combined probability, one can do find a much tighter interval if
 information 
\emph on
against
\emph default
